504. Base 7
Given an integer num, return a string of its base 7 representation.

Example 1:
Input: num = 100
Output: "202"

Example 2:
Input: num = -7
Output: "-10"
 
Constraints:
-107 <= num <= 107

Approach: Check whether output should be in integer or String
Here we are printing for String.

Logic:- 
Divide the given number by 7 and store the remainder
check if number is negative take make it positive by multiplying with -1
Then do the same with Negative number as well
Divide the number by 7 and store the remainder

Edge case:-
 0 - 6 ==> "0"
Numbers from 0 - 6 will be return as it is in String format.


Solution:-
class Solution {
    public String ReverseString(String str){  //Function to reverse the String
        String rev="";
        for (int i = str.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
             rev += str.charAt(i);
      }
      return rev;
    }
    public String convertToBase7(int num) {
        String ans="";
        int lastDigit=0;
        int negNum=num*-1; int posNum=num;
        if(num==0){
            return "0";
        }
        //Check for Negative number
        if(num < 0){
            while(negNum>0){
            lastDigit= negNum % 7 ;
            ans +=lastDigit;
            negNum=negNum/7;
            }
        }else{
         //Check for Negative number
          while(posNum>0){
            lastDigit= posNum % 7 ;
            ans +=lastDigit;
            posNum=posNum/7;
          }
        }
        if(num>0){
            return ReverseString(ans);
        }
        return ("-" + ReverseString(ans));
    }
}
